#: ../../simulator.rst:117
msgid ""
"The slope of a glacier bed is one key ingredient which determines glacier"
" flow. For an introduction, visit `antarcticglaciers.org (glacier-"
"flow)`_. In short: glaciers flow downslope driven by the gravitational "
"force. This force can be decomposed into an along-slope component and "
"perpendicular to the slope component (see `this illustration in wikipedia"
" "
"<https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Inclined_plane#/media/File:Free_body1.3.svg>`_)."
" The along-slope component \"pulls\" the glacier downwards and the "
"perpendicular component \"flattens\" the glacier."
msgstr ""

